"FIRST, we do NOT speak to the Goddesses of Olympus in such a manner!  Aphrodite is my friend and someone who HAS blessed this tribe with her presense many times," Hippolyte stopped a moment.  Trying to calm her fumming down. Then she looked to Aphrodite, "Please forgive us, Aphrodite.  It seems the heat of the moment may have gotten the best of us."<br>
Then Hippolyte's eyes turned to Alastor, tho she spoke to those around her as well. "You played an insane game to come to Themiscrya this way.  This is a village of highly loyal and protective amazons," she smiled proudly at that. "If you had sought audience with me, a scroll would have sufficed.  Now," she glanced to the others, then back to Alastor.  "Everyone please leave me for now so I can speak to this foolish man.  Alysia and my guards shall await outside the hut."<br>
Her eyes peirced to Alastor's, "And I am NOT a warrior princess...Queen will do." She raised a brow. <center><br>
