&quot;Nai Vassalissa.&quot; She smiled and walked outside to wait by the entrance. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uxgoddessaphrodite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xGoddess Aphrodite</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#993300>(7/19/01 8:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=248.topic&index=75>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.xenafan.com/gallery/official/aphrodite_02.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ::takes a seat::</span><hr size=1> ::Nods to the amazons who pay respect and finds the other little spitfire of an amazon amusing.  She takes a seat and observes the action which has been indeed more interesting since her leave of absence from Olympus.  As the Queen of Themiscrya enters she stands and smiles.::<br>
<br>
Hello Hippolyte...fancy meeting you here!  ::chuckles at her attempt to make a joke::  I finally know the reason to why  Alastor needed me...to give him a make-over!  ::shakes her head to him as to say &quot;naughty-boy&quot; :::<br>
<br>
However, I find that your tribe has a lot of honor to their lands...it good to see that.  ::returns to a sitting postion and smoothes out her dress::   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=alastorofancients>Alastor of Ancients</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#993300>(7/22/01 12:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=248.topic&index=76>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Question.</span><hr size=1> &quot;Thank you, All right here is the situation.  Rumors are coming around of tensions in the amazons lands, either from other countries or bandits killing amazons. Of course in Rome there are many rumors. As some of you know I have a slight pull in Rome seeing I am friends with Augustus. But, We had to do it in cloak and dagger strategy because of the general populations view on amazons. We had the finiest smiths in Rome forged light armor and swords for you, It was rather interesting seeing them trying to make breast plates for females. The riches are to make sure you have money for supplies if the the war actually takes place.&quot; He leans forward in the chair resting his elbows as he cast his stren blue eyes towards Hippolyte. He looks towards the goddess's out of the corner of his eye through his thick brown bangs, then back to Hippolyte. &quot;You choice on what to do with them.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugoddessartemis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goddess Artemis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Goddess</span><br>  Posts: 106<br> <font color=#993300>(7/23/01 10:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=248.topic&index=77>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/mogoddessartemis/images/artemis2.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Question.</span><hr size=1> ~looks at Alastor with an amused smirk~<br>
Bandits have not been killing Amazons, thosea re just made up stories by men who feel emasculated by women who are stronger then them. ~smiles~ And what makes you think we need Romes help? We have our own smiths to make weapons and armour, besides, Ive seen those breastplates Rome had made, and well...~tries to think of something polite to say ~ um, they are too light and thin.<br>
Maybe noone has informed you Alastor, but the Amazons arent weak women who cannot bear more weight then themselves.<br>
Of course we know how the Romans feel about the Amazons, but I assure you, just because we signed a treaty, dont mean we want them as our best friends either. There are many an Amazon who feels ten times more against Rome, then what they think of us...<br>
<br>
Naturally, it is up to Hippolyte...<br>
<br>
~chuckles~ the breastplates could always be melted down to make better ones...<br>
